{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "As negotiators gather in Paris to hammer out a new climate treaty, experts are just beginning to assess greenhouse gas emissions by cargo ships.", "abstract": "Environmentalists and others are increasingly calling for reduction of emissions from container ships, and some shipping companies and builders are adopting new efficiency standards and technology in response; shipping is responsible for only about 2.6 percent of global emissions, but number is poised to grow, with some experts predicting that by 2050 shipping could account for one-sixth of all carbon dioxide emissions. ", "section_name": "Science", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Henry", "role": "reported", "lastname": "FOUNTAIN", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By HENRY FOUNTAIN"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/12/08/science/carbon-emissions-shipping-container-ships.html", "lead_paragraph": "As negotiators gather in Paris to hammer out a new climate treaty, experts are just beginning to assess greenhouse gas emissions by cargo ships.", "headline": {"main": "Building Greener Ships, to Keep the Sea From Rising", "print_headline": "Time for a Sea Change"}, "_id": "56668e0d38f0d84cb15f724e", "word_count": "1920", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/12/08/science/08SHIPPINGJP1/08SHIPPINGJP1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/12/08/science/08SHIPPINGJP1/08SHIPPINGJP1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 399, "url": "images/2015/12/08/science/08SHIPPINGJP1/08SHIPPINGJP1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/12/08/science/08SHIPPINGJP1/08SHIPPINGJP1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "399"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/12/08/science/08SHIPPINGJP1/08SHIPPINGJP1-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumb